THEORY OF GENERALISED MOONSHINE 
CORE BLUEPRINT (RDG FORM)

1. MOONSHINE TRIPLE
A Generalised Moonshine structure is a triple:

   (A, F(A), M(A))

SID: Algebraic carrier A
   - finite group
   - lattice
   - Lie algebra / affine algebra
   - quantum group
   - subfactor / tensor category

PED: Field-theoretic engine F(A)
   - VOA
   - CFT
   - modular tensor category
   - TQFT

RDG: Modular/automorphic output M(A)
   - characters, partition functions
   - modular forms, automorphic functions
   - S,T matrices, fusion coefficients
   - knot / 3-manifold invariants

2. AXIOMS OF THE THEORY

AXIOM 1 — Field-Theoretic Realisation
   Each admissible algebraic object A canonically generates:
      F(A) = VOA/CFT/TQFT
   capturing its representation geometry.

AXIOM 2 — Modular Data Extraction
   From F(A), extract:
      S(A), T(A), N^c_ab(A)
   satisfying:
      - SL(2,Z) relations
      - Verlinde formula
      - integrality + positivity

AXIOM 3 — Automorphic Output
   Modular data + characters yield:
      M(A) = {modular forms, automorphic objects, invariants}
   with:
      - genus classification
      - congruence properties
      - Galois symmetries

AXIOM 4 — Recurrence Principle
   The same S,T,fusion structures recur across:
      VOAs, CFT, quantum groups, subfactors, TQFT, knots.
   The theory explains this recurrence.

