4. GENUS-0 AS A REGIME
Genus-0 is not the definition of Moonshine.
It is a curvature regime:
   - modular curve is a sphere
   - replication constraints
   - extreme modular symmetry

Higher-genus regimes are equally valid:
   - mapping class group representations
   - automorphic forms beyond SL(2,Z)
   - geometric Moonshine in higher dimensions

